CNCP v1 23155
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#12404: `:global(A) B` incorrectly compiles to just `A`",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:21:46.239494+00:00",
  "text": "`:global(A) B` incorrectly compiles to just `A`\n\n### Vue version\n\n@d637bd6\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nIn the minimal reproduction, open the Playground's compiled CSS tab.\n\n### What is expected?\n\n```css\nbody h1[data-v-7ba5bd90] {\n  background-color: purple;\n}\n```\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\n```css\nbody {\n  background-color: purple;\n}\n```\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\nA similar issue also applies to `:global(A) > B`.\n\nYou can just remove `:global(` and `)` to get the desired effect here, but this is just a minimal reproduction to demonstrate the issue.\n\nNote that `module` doesn't seem to have this issue, only `scoped`. `:deep` also seems to work fine.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: sfc",
    ":hammer: p3-minor-bug"
  ],
